{"TopicId":179859,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Mod for Keeping Vehicles Upright?","CreatedByName":"Mars-Bound Hokie","CreatedById":192121,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-17T04:15:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Mars-Bound Hokie","CreatedById":192121,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-17T04:15:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know if anybody has asked this before, but is there a mod I can install to keep landers/rovers\u00A0upright during landing and/or use? One time, I sent a mobile base to the Mun and it tipped over, rendering it completely useless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-17T08:45:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf they have probe core or pod pointed upwards at launch and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E module, just turn it on, change it to surface mode and click on retrograde. If you didn\u0027t have any horizontal speed, it should do its work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-17T08:53:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVesselMover Continued can be an essential mod for these kind of scenarios. It lets you pick up, rotate and lower a landed craft.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, it\u0027s a bit cheaty but if you\u0027ve spent hours on a mission only to have your lander bounce over because of poorly designed stock landing struts then you can probably forgive yourself for using this mod rather than re-running the whole mission.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-17T14:51:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo quote an old car commercial:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWider is better!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeriously though, design your base to be shorter and wider so it\u0027s naturally stable. No one needs a lighthouse on the Mun after all. Lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-17T14:56:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223488950\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179859\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542466305\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154640\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rocket In My Pocket\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Rocket In My Pocket said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo one needs a lighthouse on the Mun after all. Lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022IEhvR00.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/IEhvR00.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022720\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-17T15:00:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223488953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179859\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542466588\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-snip-\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E\u0022We\u0027re whalers on the moon, we carry our harpoons! But there aint\u0027 no whales so we tell tall tales, and sing our whaling tune!\u0022\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRofl! Great, now I\u0027ve got that song stuck in my head. (Love Futurama!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-17T15:02:08Z\u0022 title=\u002211/17/2018 03:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 17, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-17T15:21:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223488950\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179859\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542466305\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154640\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rocket In My Pocket\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, Rocket In My Pocket said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo quote an old car commercial:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWider is better!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeriously though, design your base to be shorter and wider so it\u0027s naturally stable. No one needs a lighthouse on the Mun after all. Lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaximum diameter inside an 5 meter base fairing is 15 meter. If you have to build high make the base wide. Note that you can dock outriggers in orbit\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-17T15:46:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223488961\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179859\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542468092\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n24 minutes ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaximum diameter inside an 5 meter base fairing is 15 meter. If you have to build high make the base wide. Note that you can dock outriggers in orbit\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr forget the fairings entirely!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThrust\u0026gt;Drag.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-17T17:34:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223488822\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179859\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542428154\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192121\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mars-Bound Hokie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/17/2018 at 2:15 AM, Mars-Bound Hokie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know if anybody has asked this before, but is there a mod I can install to keep landers/rovers\u00A0upright during landing and/or use? One time, I sent a mobile base to the Mun and it tipped over, rendering it completely useless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI use TweakScale for that!!! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot225.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://ksp.lisias.net/screenshots/misc/2018/11/screenshot225.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-29T01:17:47Z\u0022 title=\u002201/29/2019 01:17  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 29, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Lisias\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eupdating images URL\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}